      "rationale": "Governing equations: incompressible Navier-Stokes with SST k-omega turbulence closure; Eulerian hemolysis transport with modified Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law source term (C = 1.8e-6, alpha = 1.9914, beta = 0.7650 per Taskin et al. 2012 calibration). Model form uncertainty assessed by comparison against two alternative hemolysis models (Lagrangian particle tracking, stress-based threshold model); NIH predictions agree within 12% across all operating points. RANS turbulence model form uncertainty estimated at ±18% for TKE; propagated to NIH uncertainty via sensitivity analysis contributing S_T = 0.08. Model form assumptions (Newtonian blood, rigid walls, steady-state rotation via MRF) documented with applicability justification.",
